        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 8:08PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 808 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Pinefield Crossroads,
or near Homer, moving northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Homer, Hollingsworth, and Pinefield Crossroads.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
